This article discusses the experience of an intern working in the Office of Presidential Correspondence at the White House. The intern's role includes selecting representative pieces of mail from the public, which are included in the President's daily briefing folder. The intern also represents the White House at meetings with other federal agencies to discuss key issues facing Americans and how to better serve them. The intern reflects on the importance of teamwork and cooperation in public service and how every contribution, no matter how small, can make a difference in the lives of the American people. The intern, Said Bilani, is from Miami, Florida, and is studying Government & Public Policy and Business at Franklin & Marshall College.